            <div type="transcript" id="P91-89">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The skies can't keep their secret!</l>
                    <l>They tell it to the hills </l>
                    <l>The hills just tell the orchards </l>
                    <l>And they the daffodils!</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>A bird, by chance, that goes that way</l>
                    <l>Soft overheard the whole.</l>
                    <l>If I should bribe the little bird,</l>
                    <l>Who knows but she would tell?</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>I think I won't, however,</l>
                    <l>It's finer not to know;</l>
                    <l>If summer were an axiom,</l>
                    <l>What sorcery had snow?</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>So keep your secret, Father!</l>
                    <l>I would not, if I could,</l>
                    <l>Know what the sapphire fellows do,</l>
                    <l>In your new-fashioned world!</l>
                </lg>

            </div>     
